This paper deals with graphical models, which are widely studied in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on acyclic digraphs (ADGs) and their Markov equivalence classes, which are important concepts in probabilistic graphical models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves combinatorial analysis and algorithms, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper could also be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with modeling relationships between variables.
